This paper is likely to belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category as it deals with the task of ranking in E-commerce recommender systems. It also involves machine learning techniques such as learning a ranking function and using a transformer structure, which are commonly used in the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of personalized embeddings, which falls under the sub-category of Natural Language Processing (cs.CL). The paper also involves modeling user preferences and intents, which could be related to the sub-categories of Cybersecurity (cs.CY) and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI).
